<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent"> Health Information Center News</a></h2>

<p>
Talk About Curing Autism (TACA), a non-profit organization, provides information, resources, and support to families affected by autism. For families who have just received the autism diagnosis, TACA aims to speed up the cycle time from the autism diagnosis to effective treatments. TACA helps to strengthen the autism community by connecting families and the professionals who can help them, allowing them to share stories and information to help people with autism be the best they can be.
</p>
<p>
TACA provides "Responsible HOPE" to parents and families affected by autism.
</p>
<p>
For more information please visit <a href="http://www.tacanow.org">www.tacanow.org</a>
</p>
<p>
TACA meetings will be held at the 
<a href="http://www.hclib.org/AgenciesAction.cfm?agency=Rd">Ridgedale Public Library in Minnetonka</a>
 from 7-9pm.

</p>
<p>
The meeting schedule is as follows:
</p>
<ul>
	<li>Monday March 24th: Learn more about TACA, followed by parent discussion </li>
	<li>Monday April 28th: Guest Speaker Julia Sawyer, Parent Coordinator for Autism Matters.</li>
	<li>Tuesday May 20th: Guest Speaker Brad Trahan, parent and founder of the <a href="http://www.RTAutismAwareness.org">RT Autism Foundation</a> to speak about Autism, Legislature, and Law Enforcement</li>
	<li>Monday June 30th: Guest Speaker Amy Dawson from the Family to Family Health Center at PACER, speaking about MA/TEFRA, Waivers and CDCS</li>
</ul>

